		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://blog.brainstation.io/?p=10579</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[<p>For his Certificate project, Zac Poissant designed the ultimate public transit app to make commuting an easier experience without stress. </p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://brainstation.io/blog/project-highlight-zac-poissant-ux-design">Project Highlight: Zac Poissant, UX Design</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://brainstation.io/blog">BrainStation® Blog</a>.</p>
]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you could design any app what would you create? UX Design students at BrainStation have the opportunity to turn that question into a reality as they learn how to prototype the program they wish existed.</span></p>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For his Certificate course project, </span><a href="https://www.zacpoissant.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Zac Poissant</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> aimed to design the ultimate “all-in-one” public transit app to make commuting “easier, more efficient, and stress-free.”</span></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter"><a href="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TTC-animation-V1.gif"><img src="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TTC-animation-V1-1024x768.gif" alt="BrainStation UX design project" class="wp-image-10580" srcset="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TTC-animation-V1-1024x768.gif 1024w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TTC-animation-V1-300x225.gif 300w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TTC-animation-V1-768x576.gif 768w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TTC-animation-V1-705x529.gif 705w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TTC-animation-V1-960x720.gif 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></figure></div>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">An app like this would be appealing for many transit users, including Poissant himself, “as someone who has used the TTC (Toronto Transit Commission) regularly in the past, I was motivated to solve the problems that I and others have faced when using public transit.”</span></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter"><a href="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.43.09-PM.png"><img src="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.43.09-PM-1024x910.png" alt="UX design project" class="wp-image-10586" srcset="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.43.09-PM-1024x910.png 1024w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.43.09-PM-300x267.png 300w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.43.09-PM-768x683.png 768w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.43.09-PM-960x853.png 960w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.43.09-PM.png 1442w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></figure></div>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Poissant set out to create </span><a href="https://www.zacpoissant.com/ttc-app"><span style="font-weight: 400;">an app</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> that would allow you to save your favorite routes, get directions, and identify peak traffic hours to avoid. He also wanted the app to alert transit users to any relevant transit delays all in a beautiful, easy-to-use interface.</span></p>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To get from idea to concept to </span><a href="https://xd.adobe.com/view/ed078381-c37f-49fa-725c-a2e3b1ebf788-9b36/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">prototype</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, Poissant followed this design process:&nbsp;</span></p>



<ol><li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Define the needs of the business</span></li><li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Empathize with the user and understand the problem that exists</span></li><li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ideate solutions that meet the needs of both</span></li><li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Create a prototype to test and validate assumptions</span></li><li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Correct designs based on user feedback and repeat until the product is ready</span></li></ol>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Poissant emphasizes the last two steps in the process, believing they are essential for creating a customer-centric product.&nbsp;</span></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter"><a href="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.47.49-PM.png"><img src="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.47.49-PM-751x1024.png" alt="UX design process" class="wp-image-10588" srcset="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.47.49-PM-751x1024.png 751w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.47.49-PM-220x300.png 220w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.47.49-PM-768x1047.png 768w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.47.49-PM.png 870w" sizes="(max-width: 751px) 100vw, 751px" /></a></figure></div>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">“A useful lesson I learned in the course, is to validate our assumptions every step of the way. Test early and test often,” he says.</span></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter"><a href="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.42.51-PM.png"><img src="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.42.51-PM-1024x708.png" alt="UX design project" class="wp-image-10587" srcset="https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.42.51-PM-1024x708.png 1024w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.42.51-PM-300x207.png 300w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.42.51-PM-768x531.png 768w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.42.51-PM-960x663.png 960w, https://d1jxdyr49kipv5.cloudfront.net/prod/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Screen-Shot-2020-02-12-at-4.42.51-PM.png 1444w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></figure></div>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Having started his career in graphic design, Poissant is well equipped to transition into a product design role. But, to help in his career development, he knew some additional skills would solidify his new position. “I&#8217;ve always been a very strong visual designer but lacked experience when it came to things like user research and how to conduct a usability test.”</span></p>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A </span><a href="http://bit.ly/2vuvhEA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">UX design course</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> seemed the best way to learn those additional skills.&nbsp;</span></p>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">“The UX design course at Brainstation was immensely helpful in giving me the confidence I was looking for as a well-rounded Product Designer,” he says, adding that he does not want to stop there.&nbsp;</span></p>



<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">“I plan to work on more portfolio projects that inspire me and solve needs that I, as well as others, have. An example might be a roommate app that helps users find like-minded people who share the same values and general sleep schedule. Or perhaps a budgeting app. In addition to this, I hope to continue to work on challenging projects in real life that solve real business and user needs.”</span></p>



<p>&#8212;</p>



<p><em>Now&#8217;s the time to take a flexible, part-time <a href="http://bit.ly/2vuvhEA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">UX Certificate Course</a></em></p>
